<br>
<br>
I consider your request the same way I would a non-planar guild telling the RTA it's not fair that his friends can't kill the Tentacle Terrors in Fear, just because they aren't able to kill the Gorgons.  His ranger could use the loot, and his friends are capable of killing some of the mobs (the Tentacles) so what that they don't have 40+ members and can't kill the other mobs (Gorgons or Golems).<br>
<br>
It IS fair, just because you can kill one part of what is considered a rotation or reservation, doesn't mean you should &quot;be allowed&quot; to kill that part to the detriment of others.  By guilds forming to go after &quot;just Ikky or Eashen&quot;, you are denying the N ToV guilds their rotation mobs.  It would be like me taking NB into Fear and clearing your Tentacles for you the morning of your Fear raid, because we have a new halfling ranger who could use the armor.  You'd be pretty pissed if you had guildmates who could use that armor, wouldn't you?  <br>
<br>
Now if you want to take the argument, that &quot;hey I pay $12.95 a month too&quot;, well, we all know where that argument goes.  If NB, TL, and BotS all took our membership's collective $12.95 and ditched the rotations, you still wouldn't be killing Ikky or Eashen.  So please, don't be hypocritical and take advantage of the Planar reservation system or Rotation system and &quot;deny&quot; others the opportunity to do certain mobs, and then complain people should be allowed to take apart a rotation that has been going on for over a year.  <br>
<br>
Much like there was nothing like your first few Hate and Fear raids as a guild, alone in the area, exploring, so too is N ToV a blast the first few times you crawl through it.  It becomes much less fun when people have sniped 14.3% (2 of 14) of your raid mobs for the day on your 12th raid. <p><p><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net"><img src="http://www.noble-blade.net/images/ezboard/sig-small.gif" align="left" border="0"></a>Karadin Firethorne<br>Assassin of The Rathe<br><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net">Noble Blade</a> 
