<br>
It seems to be the general idea here that &quot;no one is saying that you can not &quot;attempt&quot; the mob even though you can kill it&quot;.  Rules are here and in place to protect everyone, big and small.  When people say &quot;no one is telling you that you can't attempt them&quot; are they missing the whole peer pressure issue??  Isnt that what the RTA is all about?  If it is deemed sniping by the 3 guilds that control NToV then the whole rathe would be behind them when it came up on the flame board.  A guild that attempted and won against them then left NToV would be poo'd on for a long time.  Granted this would be in violation of the current &quot;agreement&quot; and I understand that.  That is why I asked would it be possible to move the rotation to start at Aar.  <br>
<br>
With that said I am wondering though how can you say that it would be wrong and unfair to you and that I would be withholding your mob from you and taking away 14.3% of YOUR raid when you wouldn't even consider allowing others to ATTEMPT them unless they can clear NToV.  Because they are YOUR mob's YOU earned them by clearing NToV right? <br>
<br>
I can understand your comparision about taking  NB into Fear and clearing the tentacles.  I never once said I am against the rotations or protected mobs, I do understand this.  I understand that the GM's from NB, Tindi and BotS OWN those mobs and its their call if they want to share those 2 with others without holding them to clearing NToV, they have voiced their opinion and the law stands as it was.   I will not attempt them unless I am leading a guild that is capable of clearing all of NToV, those are the rules that were set up by the Rathe and as being part of the community I will respect those rules, but I will also question them as I feel is my right.<br>
<br>
I got my answer before and responded to it.  I don't agree with holding back mobs that people are capable of killing, that was it.  I dropped it because the argument was going no where and I got the impression that the majority didn't agreed with me.   Thats fine I can handle that.<br>
<br>
We each have our seperate views on this issue.   I can live with that, sometimes you can't agree with everyone around you, sometimes you can't control others, should you hate them then or try to hurt them by belittling them?  Or should you still respect them and their views while holding strong to that which you value?  Well thats up to you.<br>
<br>
I would like to thank all of the other posters who were cool, forthcoming and open in their responses in this discussion.<br>
<br>
On a last note I never once brought into this conversation the idea or theology of &quot;I pay 12.95 a month to play for a game I will kill what I want.&quot;  Never once did I say that or infer that.  I was talking about what I felt was a basic right of people.  Please do not put words into my mouth, suggest you know what I am thinking, or suggest I would resort to saying that.  That is rude and uncalled for.  Yes that rotation has been going on for a year like that, but as was brought up on another thread a year ago only 4 guilds were capable of killing named in ToV. <p><center><BR><font color= Blue><BR><i>Granitfist/Jeribu<i/><BR><i>GrandMaster/High Priest<i/><BR><i>Co-Leader of Circles End<i/><BR><i>The Rathe<BR><center><i><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370733">The Monk </> <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370756">The Cleric<i/>
