Just wanted to point out your righteous indignation has no business in this thread.  You did, in fact, infer the “$12.95 a month” argument, even if you didn’t get to the part of the argument that involves spelling out where this “basic right” that you speak of, comes from..  Where *does* this “basic right” for engaging mobs come from?  It comes from the argument that we all pay/play this game together and the “you’re not the boss of me” type attitude you display so brilliantly.  Your claim to have not inferred this is incorrect at best.  I’m not suggesting that I know what you were thinking, nor am I putting words if your mouth.   I am pointing out that this IS the source of the point you are making.  That we are somehow removing your “basic right” (gotten from where please?) to kill what you want when you want, and so we should change our rotation to suit your desires.<br>
<br>
Secondly, where you got the idea I was rude to you is beyond me, as I have been nothing but civil to you.  If you would prefer to see what rude looks like, I guess we can go there, but it looks much different and isn’t necessary.  All I have stated were my answers to your questions and trying to get you to understand things from my perspective, which you are still having a hard time doing.  Your responses all give lip service to “ya ya, I understand that, but why can’t I get what I want?” (paraphrased)  You talk on and on about how nice the Rathe is, and rotations are great things, and then lament that you can’t just disregard them or change them to suit you (and others), when you aren’t even on the rotation in question.  It shows no understanding at all, frankly.  Read my Fear example again, and put yourself in my place.  How would you feel if someone came and took some of &quot;your&quot; mobs before you got to Fear? <p><p><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net"><img src="http://www.noble-blade.net/images/ezboard/sig-small.gif" align="left" border="0"></a>Karadin Firethorne<br>Assassin of The Rathe<br><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net">Noble Blade</a> 
